86 records. Class of 1976 Scholarship

This scholarship was established in 2016 with a gift from an anonymous donor and offered to students who have completed Year 12 at Noble Park Secondary College or a nearby school and are experiencing difficult circumstances.

Benefits

The Class of 1976 scholarship provides a living allowance of $15,000 per year (full time rate) for three years.

Conditions

This scholarship is subject to the Coursework Scholarships Conditions and can be deferred to the following calendar year.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Undergraduate Coursework Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Airwallex Scholarship Airwallex Scholarship Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Melbourne School of Engineering Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible A. O. Capell Scholarship

The Harbison-Higinbotham Research Scholarship and A. O. Capell Scholarship were established with donations from William Harbison and Alfred Oscar Capell respectively and is offered to high-achieving students undertaking graduate research training.

Benefits

The scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • Living allowance of $36,200 per year pro rata (2020 full-time rate) for up to 2 years for Master by research students and up to 3.5 years for Doctoral students. This includes limited paid sick, maternity and parenting leave. The duration will be reduced by any study completed towards your course prior to receiving this scholarship.
  • Relocation grant of $2,000 for students moving from States or Territories other than Victoria or $3,000 for students moving from outside Australia.

Conditions

This scholarship is subject to the Graduate Research Scholarships Terms and Conditions.

In addition:

  • Commencement of the scholarship can be deferred to a following year.
  • You must acknowledge the contribution of this scholarship in any published or produced material which relate to the research project for which the scholarship was awarded.
  • You must provide a brief report on the benefits of the scholarship and give permission for the University to provide the report, your name and course details to the donor.

Should you have any queries, please refer to Manage your scholarship or contact Stop 1.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Graduate Research Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Bachelor of Arts International Bursary

The Bachelor of Arts International Bursary is awarded to a select group of high achieving international students in recognition of their excellent academic results.

Benefits
This scholarship provides a one-off allowance of $10,000 paid after the census date of your first semester of enrolment.

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the attached Arts Scholarships Terms & Conditions.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Arts Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Bachelor of Arts International Scholarship

The Bachelor of Arts International Scholarship is awarded to a select group of high achieving international students in recognition of their excellent academic results.

Benefits
This scholarship provides a 25 per cent tuition fee remission for the standard full-time duration of the Bachelor of Arts.

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the attached Bachelor of Arts Scholarship Terms & Conditions and cannot be deferred to the following academic year.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Arts Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Bachelor of Arts International Scholarship

The Bachelor of Arts International Scholarship is awarded to a select group of high achieving international students in recognition of their excellent academic results.

Benefits
This scholarship provides a 50 per cent tuition fee remission for the standard full-time duration of the Bachelor of Arts.

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the attached Bachelor of Arts Scholarship Terms & Conditions and cannot be deferred to the following academic year.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Arts Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Design Pathways Scholarship

The scholarship is offered by the Faculty of Architecture, Building and Planning to students from a regional or remote area in Victoria or students from states or territories other than Victoria to assist with their transition to the Bachelor of Design.

Benefits

The Design Pathways Scholarship provides a one-off payment of $5,000.

Conditions

  • This scholarship is subject to the Coursework Scholarships Conditions.
  • You must receive an offer and enrol in the Bachelor of Design in Semester 1, 2020.
  • You must maintain an academic status of 'Good Standing' throughout the 2020 academic year. Otherwise, you may be required to repay the scholarship amount
  • This scholarship may be held in conjunction with other University of Melbourne scholarships
  • This scholarship cannot be deferred.
Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Architecture, Building and Planning Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Bushfire Relief Grant

Conditions

The Bushfire Relief Grants are subject to the following contitions:

  • If you take leave of absence or withdraw from your course in Semester 1, 2019, you may be required to return the grant (or part thereof).
  • If your circumstances change significantly (e.g. you receive compensation for losses incurred), you must notify Melbourne Scholarships immediately. You may be required to return the grant (or part thereof).

The University will use returned funds to assist other students afftected by the Australian Bushfires.

Your bank details

You should provide or update your bank and address details as soon as possible:

  1. Log into my.unimelb
  2. Click on the ‘Student admin’ tab, and go to ‘Financial support’
  3. Select ‘View and update my bank account details’
  4. Click on ‘Update’ and enter your bank details, then click 'Save'.

The grant will be paid to you on the first available Pay Day after you have updated your bank details.

If you have any queries about this grant or the conditions, please contact Melbourne Scholarships.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Financial Aid Bursary Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible CHIP Foundation Scholarship

The CHIP Foundation Scholarship was established with a donation from Professor K. Brian Start in memory of the work of a number of special individuals whose vision and passion to meet needs of highly able children touched the lives of many children and their families. The scholarship is awarded to advanced learners who are enrolled in an undergraduadte degree and are experiencing disadvantaged circumstances.

Benefits

This scholarship provides a one-off payment of $5,000

Conditions

This scholarship is subject to the following conditions

  • You must be enrolled in an undergraduate course at the University of Melbourne
  • You must provide a brief report on the benefits of the scholarship (upon request) and give permission for the University to provide this report, your name and course details to the donor of this scholarship.
  • This scholarship can be deferred to the following calendar year.

Should you have any queries, please refer to Manage your scholarship or contact Stop 1.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Undergraduate Coursework Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Commerce Achievement Scholarship

This scholarship is offered by the Faculty of Business and Economics to talented undergraduate students who enrol in the Bachelor of Commerce in recognition of their academic achievement during their Australian Year 12 or International Baccalaureate (IB).

Benefits

The Commerce Achievement Scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • Living allowance of $8,000 per year for the standard full-time 3-year duration of the Bachelor of Commerce degree.
  • Melbourne Global Scholars Award of up to $2,500 for an approved period of overseas Exchange or Study Abroad program.

Conditions

The Commerce Achievement Scholarship is subject to the following conditions:

  • Commerce Achievement Scholarship Terms and Conditions
  • You must receive an offer for and commence the Bachelor of Commerce(including Graduate Degree Packages) at the University of Melbourne in Semester 1, 2020.
  • You must be enrolled as a full-time student. You may be eligible to receive the scholarship, if you are enrolled as a part-time student. See: Part-time enrolment
  • This scholarship cannot be deferred.
Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Business and Economics Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Curran Engineering Scholarship Curran Engineering Scholarship Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Undergraduate Coursework Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Dean's International Graduate Scholarship

The Dean's International Graduate Scholarship is awarded to high achieving international students in recognition of their excellent academic results.

Benefits
The Dean's International Graduate Scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • an one off allowance of AUD$30,000 per year for up to two years. The allowance is paid in four annual instalments in April, June, September and November.
  • a 100 per cent fee remission for the standard duration of your course

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the following conditions:

  • Commencement of this scholarship cannot be deferred, however students will be automatically reconsidered for eligibility for the deferred intake
  • You must enrol in your course as a full-time student and maintain satisfactory academic progress
  • You must be available for promotional activities and able to represent the Melbourne School of Design

See also: MSD International Scholarships

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Architecture, Building and Planning Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Dean of Science Bursary Dean of Science Bursary Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Science Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Dean of Science Excellence Award Dean of Science Excellence Award Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Science Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Dean of Science Leadership Award Dean of Science Leadership Award Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Science Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Engineering and IT Indigenous Ambassadors Scholarship Engineering and IT Indigenous Ambassadors Scholarship Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Melbourne School of Engineering Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Doctoral Program Scholarship

The Faculty of Business and Economics - Doctoral Program Scholarship was established by the University of Melbourne and is offered to high-achieving students undertaking research study within the Faculty of Business and Economics.

Benefits

The maximum duration of the scholarship is 5.5 years. The scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • Full tuition fee remission or exemption for up to 5.5 years for students undertaking a Master by research degree and Doctoral degree.
  • Living allowance of $31,200 per year pro rata (2020 full-time rate) for up to 5.5 years for students undertaking a Master by research degree and Doctoral degree. This includes limited paid sick, maternity and parenting leave. The duration will be reduced by any study completed towards your course prior to receiving this scholarship.
  • Relocation grant of $2,000 for students moving from States or Territories other than Victoria or $3,000 for students moving from outside Australia.
  • Visa length Overseas Student Health Cover (single membership) for students who require a student visa to study in Australia.

Conditions

This scholarship is subject to the Graduate Research Scholarships Terms and Conditions.

In addition:

  • Commencement of the scholarship can be deferred to a following year.
  • You must acknowledge the contribution of this scholarship in any published or produced material which relate to the research project for which the scholarship was awarded.

Should you have any queries, please refer to Manage your scholarship or contact Stop 1.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Graduate Research Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Future Generations Scholarship

The Future Generations Scholarship was established by donations to the University of Melbourne Annual Appeal to assist graduate students with meeting the cost of living and study. 

Benefits
The Future Generations Scholarship provides an allowance of $5,000 per year for up to two years. The allowance is paid in instalments in April and September. See: Scholarship Payments

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the Coursework Scholarship Conditions. Upon request, you must provide a brief report on how this scholarship has assisted you with achieving your academic aspirations.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Graduate Coursework Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Graduate School of Humanities and Social Sciences International Bursary

Benefits

The Hansen Scholarship was establiehsed with a donation from Jane Hansen and Paul Little and offered to talented undergraduate students whose circumstances present a challenge to accessing a first-class education.

Benefits

The Hansen Scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • a standard room, at no charge, at Little Hall in Lincoln Square South for 48 weeks per year for three years
  • a living allowance of $4,000 per year for three years
  • a full fee remission for holders of a temporary Australian Humanitarian visa
  • access to tailored pastoral care mentoring and development programs
  • a one-time grant of up to $4,000 to support an approved activity for the Scholar's development (e.g. overseas study or an internship)
  • priority access to graduate accommodation at Little Hall if you wish to pursue graduate studies at Melbourne
  • next steps funding after completion of your undergraduate degree for up to $10,000 for a short-term activity or up to $20,000 for further study

Conditions

These scholarships are subject to the Coursework Scholarships Conditions and cannot be deferred to the following calendar year unless there are compelling circumstances that prevent you from commencing your course in the year following completion of Year 12. In addition:

  • You must achieve an average result of at least 60 in each semester of enrolment
  • You must reside at Little Hall for the duration of the undergraduate degree, and commit to participation in a program of scholarship and enrichment activities as determined the Director of the Hansen Scholarship.

Conditions

The Bushfire Relief Grants are subject to the following contitions:

  • If you take leave of absence or withdraw from your course in Semester 1, 2019, you may be required to return the grant (or part thereof).
  • If your circumstances change significantly (e.g. you receive compensation for losses incurred), you must notify Melbourne Scholarships immediately. You may be required to return the grant (or part thereof).

The University will use returned funds to assist other students afftected by the Australian Bushfires.

Your bank details

You should provide or update your bank and address details as soon as possible:

  1. Log into my.unimelb
  2. Click on the ‘Student admin’ tab, and go to ‘Financial support’
  3. Select ‘View and update my bank account details’
  4. Click on ‘Update’ and enter your bank details, then click 'Save'.

The grant will be paid to you on the first available Pay Day after you have updated your bank details.

If you have any queries about this grant or the conditions, please contact Melbourne Scholarships.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Architecture, Building and Planning Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Dean of Science Bursary Dean of Science Bursary Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Science Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Dean of Science Excellence Award Dean of Science Excellence Award Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Science Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Dean of Science Leadership Award Dean of Science Leadership Award Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Science Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Engineering and IT Indigenous Ambassadors Scholarship Engineering and IT Indigenous Ambassadors Scholarship Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Melbourne School of Engineering Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Doctoral Program Scholarship

The Faculty of Business and Economics - Doctoral Program Scholarship was established by the University of Melbourne and is offered to high-achieving students undertaking research study within the Faculty of Business and Economics.

Benefits

The maximum duration of the scholarship is 5.5 years. The scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • Full tuition fee remission or exemption for up to 5.5 years for students undertaking a Master by research degree and Doctoral degree.
  • Living allowance of $31,200 per year pro rata (2020 full-time rate) for up to 5.5 years for students undertaking a Master by research degree and Doctoral degree. This includes limited paid sick, maternity and parenting leave. The duration will be reduced by any study completed towards your course prior to receiving this scholarship.
  • Relocation grant of $2,000 for students moving from States or Territories other than Victoria or $3,000 for students moving from outside Australia.
  • Visa length Overseas Student Health Cover (single membership) for students who require a student visa to study in Australia.

Conditions

This scholarship is subject to the Graduate Research Scholarships Terms and Conditions.

In addition:

  • Commencement of the scholarship can be deferred to a following year.
  • You must acknowledge the contribution of this scholarship in any published or produced material which relate to the research project for which the scholarship was awarded.

Should you have any queries, please refer to Manage your scholarship or contact Stop 1.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Graduate Research Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Future Generations Scholarship

The Future Generations Scholarship was established by donations to the University of Melbourne Annual Appeal to assist graduate students with meeting the cost of living and study. 

Benefits
The Future Generations Scholarship provides an allowance of $5,000 per year for up to two years. The allowance is paid in instalments in April and September. See: Scholarship Payments

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the Coursework Scholarship Conditions. Upon request, you must provide a brief report on how this scholarship has assisted you with achieving your academic aspirations.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Graduate Coursework Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Fay Marles Scholarship

The Fay Marles Scholarship was established by The University of Melbourne and named after former Chancellor Ms Fay Marles. The scholarship is offered to students from Australian Indigenous descent or students who are experiencing compassionate or compelling circumstances.

Benefits

The scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • Living allowance of $31,200 per year pro rata (2020 full-time rate) for up to 2 years for Master by research students and up to 3.5 years for Doctoral students. This includes limited paid sick, maternity and parenting leave. The duration will be reduced by any study completed towards your course prior to receiving this scholarship.
  • Relocation grant of $2,000 for students moving from States or Territories other than Victoria or $3,000 for students moving from outside Australia.

Conditions

This scholarship is subject to the Graduate Research Scholarships Terms and Conditions.

In addition:

  • Commencement of the scholarship can be deferred to a following year.
  • You must acknowledge the contribution of this scholarship in any published or produced material which relate to the research project for which the scholarship was awarded.
  • You must provide a brief report on the benefits of the scholarship and give permission for the University to provide the report, your name and course details to the donor.

Should you have any queries, please refer to Manage your scholarship or contact Stop 1.

Scholarship Offering Number 2 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add Graduate School of Humanities and Social Sciences International Bursary

The Graduate School of Humanities and Social Sciences International Bursary is awarded to a select group of high achieving international students in recognition of their excellent academic results.

Benefits
This scholarship provides a one-off allowance of $10,000 paid after the census date of your first semester of enrolment.

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the following conditions:

  • You must be enrolled as a full-time international student in a Master degree program offered by the Faculty of Arts.
  • This scholarship cannot be deferred to the following academic year.
Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Arts Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Graduate School of Humanities and Social Sciences International Scholarship

The Graduate School of Humanities and Social Sciences International Scholarship is awarded to a select group of high achieving international students in recognition of their excellent academic results.

Benefits
This scholarship provides a 10 per cent tuition fee remission for the standard full-time duration of your course.

Conditions
This scholarship is subject to the attached GSHSS International Scholarship Terms & Conditions and cannot be deferred to the following academic year.

Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Arts Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Graduate School of Humanities and Social Sciences Top Up Scholarship Graduate School of Humanities and Social Sciences Top Up Scholarship Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Faculty of Arts Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Hansen Scholarship

The Hansen Scholarship was establiehsed with a donation from Jane Hansen and Paul Little and offered to talented undergraduate students whose circumstances present a challenge to accessing a first-class education.

Benefits

The Hansen Scholarship provides the following benefits:

  • a standard room, at no charge, at Little Hall in Lincoln Square South for 48 weeks per year for three years
  • a living allowance of $4,000 per year for three years
  • a full fee remission for holders of a temporary Australian Humanitarian visa
  • access to tailored pastoral care mentoring and development programs
  • a one-time grant of up to $4,000 to support an approved activity for the Scholar's development (e.g. overseas study or an internship)
  • priority access to graduate accommodation at Little Hall if you wish to pursue graduate studies at Melbourne
  • next steps funding after completion of your undergraduate degree for up to $10,000 for a short-term activity or up to $20,000 for further study

Conditions

These scholarships are subject to the Coursework Scholarships Conditions and cannot be deferred to the following calendar year unless there are compelling circumstances that prevent you from commencing your course in the year following completion of Year 12. In addition:

  • You must achieve an average result of at least 60 in each semester of enrolment
  • You must reside at Little Hall for the duration of the undergraduate degree, and commit to participation in a program of scholarship and enrichment activities as determined the Director of the Hansen Scholarship.
Online Application Dates 1-Jan-2020 to 31-Dec-2020 Offering Bestowal Year 2020 Description Undergraduate Coursework Scholarship Offering Number 1 Owning Organisational Unit Student Administration Add E Eligible Helen Macpherson Smith Scholarship

The Helen Macpherson Smith Scholarship was established with a donation from the Helen Macpherson Smith Trust and is offered to female students undertaking research study in scientific or technical disciplines or humanities and social sciences.

This scholarship is just one of many opportunities made possible because of the generosity of others who placed such high value on tertiary education and research. We hope this inspires you to become involved in the Campaign for the University of Melbourne.

Benefits

The scholarship provides a living allowance of $5,000 per year pro rata (2020 full-time rate) for up to one year.

Conditions

This scholarship is subject to the Graduate Research Scholarships Terms and Conditions.

In addition:

  • Commencement of the scholarship can be deferred to a following year.
  • This scholarship can be held concurrently with another graduate research scholarship.
  • You must acknowledge the contribution of this scholarship in any published or produced material which relate to the research project for which the scholarship was awarded.
  • You must provide a brief report on the benefits of the scholarship and give permission for the University to provide the report, your name and course details to the donor.

Should you have any queries, please refer to Manage your scholarship or contact Stop 1.

  • Relocation grant of $2,000 for students moving from States or Territories other than Victoria or $3,000 for students moving from outside Australia.

Conditions
